  print(1)
  print(2)
  print(3)

body_attrs <- attributes(body(foo))
new_body <- quote({"a";"b";"c"})
attributes(new_body) <- body_attrs
body(foo) <- new_body
attributes(foo) <- fun_attrs
debug(foo)

I've been staying up late and working evenings + weekends for a couple weeks now splitting {overedge} up into several smaller packages (+ a bunch of refactoring).

Hoping the results are easier to maintain + maybe more relevant to more users. #overedge #rstats

My varied grab bag of spatial data read, write, transform, and convert functions are now in the {sfext} package.

Docs are a little messy but IMHO there is so much good stuff in this package! https://t.co/Urnse0z6zu #rstats #rspatial #sfext

The data access functions from {overedge} including get_location + get_location_data are now in the {getdata} package https://t.co/b4OUxSzdQM #getdata

I also added a few new functions including a (barely documented) Airtable data access function https://t.co/a0ZrGw4LnC #rstats

The third package I split off is {maplayer}. This includes the layer_location_data and layer_neatline functions from {overedge} https://t.co/1mcUWtLpcz

This package only support #ggplot2 mapping right now but I'm hoping to add more #tmap layers in the future. #rstats

I expect to set up be one more spin-off package of utilities for w/ paper, margins, + other issues when going #ggplot2 to print, e.g. https://t.co/laW21Esmst 

FWIW I also expect to maintain {overedge} as a tidyverse style pkg you can use to load everything at once. #rstats
